Sentencas: The DRT method was applied to analyze the AC impedance spectra for anode-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).

Sentencas: The anode microstructure has a more severe effect on the electrochemical properties of the anode-supported microtubular SOFCs because of the small inside diameter and thickness of the anode.
Titulo: AC impedance characteristics for anode-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For example, the maximum current density and fuel utilization for the cells sintered at 1400 degrees C were lower than that at 1350 degrees C due to the low porosity of the anode.
Titulo: AC impedance characteristics for anode-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, it is difficult to separate the anode and cathode impedances by the general method of complex non-linear least squares (CNLS) with equivalent circuit models, because several components overlap for the impedance spectra measured between the anode and cathode without a reference electrode.

Sentencas: The DRT method can easily separate the impedance spectra into five polarization components for the anode-supported microtubular SOFCs.
Titulo: AC impedance characteristics for anode-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The activation energy of the anode diffusion resistance was only 24-33 kJ/mol.

Sentencas: The walls of the pores in the anode were relatively well-packed with the nickel and YSZ particles for the cells made by the use of acrylic resin as a pore former.
